track_notes: From Skookumchuk follow signs to Premier Lake Provincial Park.Stop and park at the large sign on the road announcing entry to the Park. From the parking spot walk south and east, rising up on to the broad, wooded ridge until a barbed wire fence is intersected. Alternatively walk 200m east on the road to a cattle grid and follow the fence south from the cattle grid. The fence goes almost to the summit, but there are occasionally side fences running north west from the main fence, so check your compass direction periodically, especially on descent.
